<div class="container">

    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h4 class="page-header">About:</h4>
            <p>My Smart Photo Album was created by Tya Cao for the final project of the Web Development Immersive course at General Assembly. This application was built using Ruby Sinatra and Google Vision API for image recognition.</p>
            <p>To use this application, upload an image (be careful as these images will be public!) and the application will automatically tag the image with labels based on things that are seen in the image. You can then search for the image using these labels! Try uploading a photo of a dog and then search for it using the word "dog"! :)</p>

        </div>

    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">

    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h4 class="page-header">Upload image:</h4>

            <div class="form-group">
                <form action="/photo" method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                    <div class="input-group">
                        <div class="input-group-addon">
                            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-search"></span>
                        </div>

                        <input type="file" class="form-control" name="image" id="image-selector">
                        <span class="input-group-btn">
                            <button type="submit" id="upload-button" class="btn btn-default">Upload image</button>
                        </span>

                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>

        </div>

    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">

    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h4 class="page-header">Search images:</h4>
            <p>
                <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-tags"></span>
                To display all photos, search "all"</p>

            <select class="multiple-searchbar" multiple="multiple" style="width: 90%">
                <% @photolabels.sort.each do |photolabel| %>
                <option value="<%= photolabel %>"><%= photolabel %></option>
                <% end %>
            </select>

            <button class="btn btn-default" id="selected-labels">Search</button>
        </div>

    </div>

</div>

<div class="container">

    <div class="row">

        <div class="col-lg-12">
            <h4 class="page-header">Album:</h4>
        </div>

        <div id="image-board"></div>

    </div>
</div>
